to avoid going to Vietnam?

15:28.528 --> 15:32.635
Not to be cynical, but who didn't try to get
into the Guard to avoid 'Nam back then?

15:32.865 --> 15:34.538
Me.

15:34.801 --> 15:37.975
Bush's trainer in the 147th
said he wanted to go to Vietnam.

15:38.204 --> 15:42.653
There's only one document that deals
with that in the official record.

15:42.875 --> 15:47.381
On the question
of desiring overseas transfer...

15:47.914 --> 15:48.949
Bush checked no.

15:49.148 --> 15:52.061
Bush's trainer said
that must have been a mistake.

15:52.251 --> 15:56.063
- Because that's a question you get wrong.
- Two, why did he skip his physical?

15:56.255 --> 15:59.998
Well, ifs not like he had a drug problem.
He just liked the way it smelled.

16:00.226 --> 16:02.263
Okay, three.

16:02.462 --> 16:06.740
If someone did get him into the Guard,
then who?

16:07.800 --> 16:10.781
How the hell do we get them
to go on the record?

16:10.970 --> 16:12.779
Forty-one percent say...

16:12.939 --> 16:15.783
<i>they want Mr. Bush reelected,
while 51 percent don't.</i>

16:15.942 --> 16:19.355
Is it that time of year again already...

16:19.579 --> 16:25.120
when I have to fend off the advances
of a beautiful woman such as yourself?

16:25.318 --> 16:30.825
Governor, you got the president of the
United States into the National Guard.

16:31.023 --> 16:34.436
I mean, my God,
I find that very impressive.

16:34.594 --> 16:37.507
Ha. It is impressive, isn't it?

16:37.697 --> 16:39.438
Come on TV, tell us all about it.

16:39.599 --> 16:42.375
<i>Oh, we both knew if I ever said that...</i>

16:42.602 --> 16:47.210
"about Texas' favorite son on camera,
I'd be run out of Austin on a rail."

16:47.440 --> 16:49.181
No, sorry, Mary.

16:49.375 --> 16:52.686
Johnny's gonna win this thing, anyway.

16:54.480 --> 16:56.653
<i>Barnes is still</i> a <i>no. Who's next?</i>

16:57.116 --> 17:00.120
Colonel Jerry Killian.
Bush's CO in the 111th.

17:00.319 --> 17:02.560
If anyone will know what really went on,
he will.

17:02.788 --> 17:04.028
Small problem there.

17:04.223 --> 17:06.396
- Which is?
- Killian's dead.

17:06.692 --> 17:07.727
Huh.

17:08.493 --> 17:11.202
- That's a pickle.
- Who's next?

17:11.396 --> 17:12.535
General Buck Staudt.

17:12.732 --> 17:16.305
Former CO
of Bush's 147th Interceptor Squadron.

17:16.502 --> 17:18.742
<i>George was
one of the best pilots I ever had.</i>

17:18.971 --> 17:21.178
<i>So Tm gonna respectfully invite you
to go fuck yourself.</i>

17:23.409 --> 17:24.648
General Bobby Hodges...

17:24.844 --> 17:28.587
succeeded Staudt as commander
of the 147th, Killian's direct supervisor.

17:28.814 --> 17:30.487
My husband says...

17:30.650 --> 17:32.011
<i>no strings were pulled for him.</i>

17:32.151 --> 17:34.392
<i>Now, please stop calling our house.</i>

17:36.722 --> 17:38.998
Maurice Udell, Bush's ﬂight instructor.

17:39.191 --> 17:40.864
No strings were pulled for him.

17:41.060 --> 17:43.460
<i>I thought he'd be</i> a <i>great American
and</i> a <i>great fighter pilot.</i>

17:45.932 --> 17:47.377
Tom Honeycutt.

17:47.567 --> 17:49.410
<i>No strings were putted.</i>

17:51.671 --> 17:52.877
Albert Lloyd.

17:53.072 --> 17:54.272
<i>No strings were putted.</i>

17:55.541 --> 17:56.576
Motherf...

17:59.178 --> 18:00.521
Bill Hollowell.

18:00.713 --> 18:02.056
<i>No strings were putted.</i>

18:02.248 --> 18:04.194
<i>And even if they were, it's a non issue,.</i>

18:04.383 --> 18:06.863
<i>Hey! Hey! Move, you son of</i> a <i>bitch!</i>

18:13.793 --> 18:16.273
<i>It was like they were given talking points.</i>

18:16.429 --> 18:19.103
<i>He was</i>
a <i>great guy, no strings were pulled.</i>

18:19.298 --> 18:22.768
Well, devil's advocate, Mary.
What if no strings were pulled?

18:22.969 --> 18:25.279
You know who else was in the 147th?

18:25.471 --> 18:26.711
Lloyd Bentsen's son...

18:26.906 --> 18:29.477
John Connally's son,
both of Sid Adger's sons...

18:29.709 --> 18:32.883
H.L. Hunt's grandson,
the heirs to the Sakowitz fortune...

18:33.079 --> 18:36.060
<i>and half the starting line
of the Dallas Cowboys.</i>

18:36.248 --> 18:38.228
Yeah, I'm sure ifs just a coincidence.

18:38.751 --> 18:40.924
So, what's our next move?

18:42.922 --> 18:45.163
I have no idea.

18:46.092 --> 18:48.766
<i>- I served with John Kerry.
- I served with John Kerry.</i>

18:48.961 --> 18:52.408
<i>Kerry has not been honest
about what happened in Vietnam.</i>

18:52.598 --> 18:53.770
<i>He is lying about his record.</i>

18:53.966 --> 18:57.175
I know John Kerry is lying
about his first Purple Heart...

18:57.403 --> 18:58.814
<i>"because I treated him."</i>

18:59.005 --> 19:01.076
<i>John Kerry lied to get his Bronze Star.</i>

19:01.273 --> 19:02.874
<i>I know, I was there,
I saw what happened.</i>

19:04.276 --> 19:07.746
<i>His account of what happened
and what actually happened...</i>

19:07.947 --> 19:10.518
<i>are the difference
between night and day.</i>

19:10.750 --> 19:12.286
Who is that?

19:12.485 --> 19:14.294
My secret lover, go back to sleep.

19:14.487 --> 19:17.593
<i>Have you ever heard of Linda Starr?</i>

19:17.923 --> 19:18.958
Mm-hm.

19:19.158 --> 19:22.696
<i>She runs this website, it's like
a Gearing house for anti-Bush stuff.</i>

19:22.928 --> 19:27.001
<i>She's hinting documents
are gonna be leaked soon.</i>

19:27.767 --> 19:29.110
What kind of documents?

19:30.136 --> 19:32.138
Mary Mapes is on line two.

19:32.338 --> 19:33.976
Thank you.

19:35.207 --> 19:37.483
- Mary.
<i>- I think we've got something.</i>

19:37.677 --> 19:39.782
Anti-Bush, Internet rabble-rouser.

19:39.979 --> 19:44.894
Oh, God, I talked to her for three hours,
but she put me in touch with her source.

19:45.117 --> 19:47.324
A colonel
who says he may have access...

19:47.520 --> 19:50.126
to missing documents
in Bush's purged Guard file.

19:50.289 --> 19:51.223
Sounds promising.

19:51.249 --> 19:53.887
I got Mike Smith talking
to him right now.

19:54.060 --> 19:56.904
<i>- Milk?
- Get a look at those documents.</i>

19:57.129 --> 20:00.508
And do some background on the colonel,
make sure he isn't nuts.

20:05.171 --> 20:06.343
Thank you.

20:06.672 --> 20:08.481
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

20:10.009 --> 20:12.421
Ahem. No. I saw it.

20:12.812 --> 20:16.658
I saw it with my own two eyes. Those
parts of Bush's file they didn't like...

20:16.849 --> 20:19.557
- they tossed in the wastebasket.
- Do you have these?

20:19.752 --> 20:23.529
Bill tried to talk about this in 2000,
someone ran us off the road one night.

20:23.723 --> 20:27.694
- I ain't scared of them.
- Well, I am. I am scared.

20:28.194 --> 20:32.609
All right, uh, let's say
I have the documents.

20:32.932 --> 20:36.903
Why should I show them to you?
Why not one of the newspapers?

20:37.103 --> 20:40.744
- Because nobody reads newspapers.
- One of the other networks, then.

20:40.940 --> 20:43.716
Don't know if you've noticed,
there's not too many people...

20:43.876 --> 20:46.049
who actually do
what we do anymore.

20:46.245 --> 20:49.249
We're 60 Minutes.
We're the gold standard.

20:49.448 --> 20:51.359
We can help you.

20:52.418 --> 20:54.455
Look, you come on camera...

20:54.687 --> 20:56.633
No. No. No cameras.

20:56.856 --> 20:58.392
Our name stays out of this.

20:58.557 --> 21:01.094
They will destroy us for this,
don't you understand?

21:01.293 --> 21:05.139
Nicki, listen.
I know what ifs like to be bullied.

21:05.364 --> 21:08.709
To feel like they're too strong,
and you're small and powerless.

21:08.901 --> 21:10.539
But you're not.

21:10.736 --> 21:12.738
And doing this will show them that.

21:13.105 --> 21:14.311
Now, I promise...

21:14.540 --> 21:17.146
we will protect you.

21:49.909 --> 21:53.186
- These are signed by Jerry Killian.
- Yes, they are.

21:54.313 --> 21:55.621
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

21:56.615 --> 21:58.816
The first one says
that Bush made no attempt...

21:58.984 --> 22:01.828
to meet his training certification.

22:02.021 --> 22:05.298
That is a big difference
than just missing his physical.

22:05.491 --> 22:08.938
And the second one
refers to his pilot position as critical.

22:09.128 --> 22:12.871
Well, Bush said he stopped ﬂying
because they no longer needed pilots.

22:13.098 --> 22:16.705
Mm-hm. But this document
would prove that statement untrue.

22:16.936 --> 22:19.644
Can you think of anybody
who'd wanna fool you with these...

22:19.805 --> 22:21.876
like a political dirty trick?

22:23.175 --> 22:25.815
I can't think of anyone
who would hate me that much.

22:26.011 --> 22:28.389
And do you have the originals
of these?

22:28.614 --> 22:31.288
No. No, I was only given copies.

22:32.017 --> 22:35.624
And don't ask me where I got them,
I'm not gonna tell you anything else.

22:35.821 --> 22:38.995
You get your own experts if you want to,
you have them look at them.

22:39.191 --> 22:41.000
We will.

22:42.828 --> 22:44.739
September 15th,
we don't have a show.

22:44.964 --> 22:46.841
<i>CBS is running
The Billy Graham Crusade.</i>

22:47.032 --> 22:48.568
What <i>about</i> the <i>22nd?</i>

22:48.734 --> 22:51.237
Preempted again. Dr. Phil special.

22:51.470 --> 22:53.882
So our air date is decided
by an unholy conﬂuence...

22:54.039 --> 22:56.383
between Billy Graham
and Dr. Phil McGraw?

22:56.809 --> 22:59.813
- Jesus.
- News doesn't pay the bills.

23:00.145 --> 23:01.556
There is one more option.

23:01.914 --> 23:05.157
- The 8th.
- As in five days from now?

23:07.519 --> 23:09.692
<i>- If you don't think...
- I need interviews.</i>

23:09.889 --> 23:13.359
I need to get the whole team to New York
and I need... First, I need Dan.

23:13.559 --> 23:14.731
Where is he?

23:14.927 --> 23:18.898
<i>Hurricane Frances
is pounding the Florida coast...</i>

23:19.098 --> 23:22.545
<i>harder than</i> a <i>strongman trying
to win</i> a <i>Kewpie doll at</i> a <i>carnival!</i>

23:22.735 --> 23:24.772
I'm gonna kill him.

23:27.907 --> 23:30.114
You may not have to.

23:30.609 --> 23:35.024
Maybe I can get him on a puddle jumper
to Austin for the Strong interview.

23:35.214 --> 23:39.594
I got an e-mail from the colonel about
the documents saying, "I feel better."

23:43.856 --> 23:45.699
- Yeah?
- A memorandum for record...

23:45.891 --> 23:47.529
is a memo to nobody, right'?

23:47.726 --> 23:49.535
<i>So why does Killian file them?</i>

23:49.695 --> 23:53.575
Well, Killian knows suspending a guy
this protected is a big deal.

23:53.766 --> 23:57.771
He's trying to do the right thing here, but
he needs a paper trail to insulate himself.

23:57.970 --> 24:01.816
Which means Bush's protection
must've come from higher up than Killian.

24:02.975 --> 24:04.420
You're thinking Hodges?

24:04.610 --> 24:08.217
He was Killian's direct supervisor.
I'll call you back.

24:17.423 --> 24:19.743
<i>You have
reached the Hodges' residence.</i>

24:19.758 --> 24:21.760
<i>Please leave a message.</i>

24:22.661 --> 24:24.902
<i>General Hodges,
Mary Mapes from</i> 60 <i>Minutes.</i>

24:25.097 --> 24:27.475
I was wondering
if you could give me a call back.

24:27.666 --> 24:29.737
Holy shit!

24:29.902 --> 24:34.351
Oh, ho, ho, you gotta see this.
It's a video from a cell phone...

24:34.573 --> 24:37.019
at a Democratic fundraiser.

24:38.444 --> 24:39.565
<i>Now... Thank you. Thank you.</i>

24:39.678 --> 24:43.455
<i>Now, let's talk about John Kerry
and George Bush...</i>

24:43.649 --> 24:46.653
<i>- Is that Ben Barnes?
- And I'm not name-dropping.</i>

24:48.187 --> 24:51.464
<i>You see, I got a young man
named George Bush...</i>

24:51.657 --> 24:53.377
<i>into the Air National Guard
when I was...</i>

24:53.525 --> 24:55.835
<i>- . "lieutenant governor of Texas'"
- Oh...</i>

24:56.028 --> 24:58.770
<i>Now, I'm not necessarily
proud of that, but...</i>

24:58.964 --> 25:00.671
Holy shit!

25:00.866 --> 25:05.542
I didn't know they were taping me.
Did you see it? I looked like shit!

25:05.771 --> 25:10.117
- I thought you looked wonderful, Ben.
- Oh, don't you start.

25:10.275 --> 25:13.449
The cat's already out of the bag
and your man Kerry's 10 points down.

25:13.645 --> 25:17.491
We're airing this piece in five days.
Are you in or not?

25:18.217 --> 25:20.959
- We got him! We got Barnes!
- Burkett just called.

25:21.153 --> 25:24.157
- He's got more memos to hand off.
- We need to find his source.

25:24.356 --> 25:26.199
- Okay.
- Be at the airport in the morning.

25:26.358 --> 25:29.498
<i>- I'll</i> fax you when I get there.
- Yes!

25:33.032 --> 25:36.377
"Bush wasn't here during rating
and I don't have any feedback..."

25:36.568 --> 25:43.144
"from 187th in Alabama. I will not rate.
Austin is not happy either."

25:44.476 --> 25:46.752
"Bush was not here
during rating period."

25:46.979 --> 25:51.928
They're trying to get Killian to file a
rating for Bush while he wasn't even on base.

25:52.885 --> 25:55.729
This is proof he was AWOL.

26:00.526 --> 26:02.597
Who do I talk to first?

26:02.828 --> 26:06.833
Is there any doubt in your mind
that these memos are genuine?

26:07.166 --> 26:11.342
Well, they are compatible with the way
business was done at that time.

26:11.537 --> 26:14.780
They are compatible with the man
that I remember Jerry Killian being.

26:15.007 --> 26:17.783
And what do you think Colonel Killian
was trying to do?

26:18.010 --> 26:20.684
I think he was trying
to get a duty performed...

26:20.879 --> 26:25.225
and he was trying to protect himself
because of the political environment.

26:25.417 --> 26:29.797
So political considerations
were a major force in the Guard?

26:34.259 --> 26:38.537
It verged on outright corruption,
the favors that were done...

26:38.730 --> 26:41.108
the power that was traded.

26:41.533 --> 26:44.139
From a moral and ethical standpoint...

26:44.870 --> 26:46.747
it was unconscionable.

26:49.241 --> 26:51.243
Let's go to New York.

27:00.385 --> 27:02.763
I didn't get a chance
to introduce myself.

27:02.955 --> 27:05.128
- Dan Rather.
- No shit.

27:05.324 --> 27:08.134
I mean, I'm Mike Smith. I'm familiar...

27:08.327 --> 27:11.501
I mean... I... I... I'm... Hello.

27:12.164 --> 27:15.737
You know, Mary tells me you're the one
that calls me "the old man."

27:15.934 --> 27:21.077
Well, I... I really wish
she hadn't shared that with you.

27:22.574 --> 27:26.454
Look, I appreciate the hard work
you're doing on this.

27:26.645 --> 27:29.251
Asking questions, that's important.

27:29.448 --> 27:31.826
Some people are gonna say
it doesn't matter.

27:32.017 --> 27:34.964
One side or the other's always gonna say
you're being partisan.

27:35.154 --> 27:38.499
But you stop asking questions,
that's when the American people lose.

27:38.690 --> 27:41.330
Now, that may sound hokey,
but I believe it.

27:41.627 --> 27:43.664
So keep it up.

27:43.862 --> 27:48.208
<i>Y- Yeah-Or no. Thank you.</i>

27:48.433 --> 27:51.039
- You're welcome.
- Heh.

27:53.338 --> 27:55.477
You know what's crazy?

27:56.208 --> 27:58.381
Many things are crazy.

27:58.610 --> 28:02.649
Tell me specifically
what you feel is crazy.

28:02.848 --> 28:06.159
The fact that they kept this secret
for so long.

28:09.655 --> 28:13.694
You do know why Mary didn't get
this story done in 2000, don't you?

28:13.859 --> 28:15.236
Uh-uh.

28:19.631 --> 28:21.838
Mary's mother died...

28:22.034 --> 28:24.139
right in the middle of it.

28:24.736 --> 28:28.548
And then the story never got finished
and the election happened.

28:28.740 --> 28:33.246
An election that was decided
by 537 votes.

28:33.912 --> 28:34.982
I think...

28:35.747 --> 28:38.694
that if Mary's mother
hadn't died that summer...

28:38.884 --> 28:42.730
there's a real good chance that
Al Gore would be president right now.

28:46.592 --> 28:48.902
And what about her father?

28:52.231 --> 28:55.075
Mary's father
is a drunken piece of shit...

28:55.267 --> 28:58.441
who hated himself so much,
he beat his own daughters.

29:00.239 --> 29:04.187
The more outspoken they were,
she <i>says,</i> the harder he hit them.

29:04.376 --> 29:07.289
- So how do you think she fared?
- She would get beat up...

29:07.512 --> 29:10.755
- for asking questions?
- That's right.

29:11.617 --> 29:14.564
And this is what she does for a living?

29:15.187 --> 29:17.360
People are funny sometimes.

29:19.057 --> 29:22.527
It's part of what's between her and Dan,
I think.

29:22.728 --> 29:25.265
Why they work so well together.

29:26.098 --> 29:28.544
It's why they need each other.

29:33.205 --> 29:35.481
Fathers and daughters.

29:48.420 --> 29:50.764
Whatever <i>it</i> takes.

29:51.456 --> 29:53.163
Tell me about the document examiners.

29:53.392 --> 29:57.397
There are four. Marcel Matley is coming
from San Francisco to do on-camera.

29:57.596 --> 30:00.099
Linda James in Texas
wants to see the originals.

30:00.299 --> 30:02.404
- Yeah, we don't have them.
- I told her.

30:02.601 --> 30:05.081
Jim Pierce in Los Angeles
just started today...

30:05.270 --> 30:08.274
and Emily Will in North Carolina
wants you to call her.

30:08.473 --> 30:09.611
Right. Got it.

30:09.975 --> 30:11.977
<i>I mink you have a problem.</i>

30:12.177 --> 30:14.282
I've been doing Internet research.

30:14.479 --> 30:18.325
President was in Alabama when
these were written, they can't be true.

30:18.483 --> 30:21.953
Okay. Have you found anything wrong
with the documents themselves?

30:22.154 --> 30:25.863
- Well, no, but...
- Do they appear forged in any way?

30:26.091 --> 30:28.128
- Without the originals...
- That's <i>okay.</i>

30:28.327 --> 30:30.933
You just let me worry
about the investigational side.

30:31.463 --> 30:33.966
I always work the whole thing.

30:34.499 --> 30:37.309
Look, do you know
where these originated?

30:37.502 --> 30:39.880
<i>Establishing chain of custody
would go</i> a <i>long</i> way...

30:40.038 --> 30:42.018
<i>"inward determining authenticity."</i>

30:42.207 --> 30:44.448
Yeah, believe me, we're working on it.

30:44.643 --> 30:48.455
I give you the memos, you verify them,
that was the deal.

30:48.647 --> 30:50.490
You call the Kerry campaign
for me yet?

30:50.682 --> 30:52.787
<i>They cannot lie down
on this Swift Boat shit.</i>

30:52.984 --> 30:58.491
If you could just confirm where you got
the memos from, we would be home free.

30:58.690 --> 31:01.534
- I told you I cannot go on the record.
- I <i>know.</i>

31:01.727 --> 31:04.139
I know. You wouldn't have to.

31:04.363 --> 31:08.004
You just give me the name.
All right? That's all I need.

31:11.303 --> 31:12.543
George Conn.

31:13.171 --> 31:15.014
<i>- Buddy of mine in the Guard.
- Right.</i>

31:15.207 --> 31:18.518
<i>He was there for the scrubbing.
But you call him, he will deny it.</i>

31:18.710 --> 31:21.816
- Thank you.
- Goodbye.

31:28.820 --> 31:31.061
<i>You have reached the Conn residence.</i>

31:31.223 --> 31:32.224
<i>Please leave a message.</i>

31:33.759 --> 31:36.171
Colonel, this is Mary Mapes
with 60 Minutes.

31:36.361 --> 31:39.205
Was wondering if you could give me
a call at your convenience.

31:39.398 --> 31:43.869
It's regarding a story we're airing
on Wednesday night. Thank you.

31:44.069 --> 31:45.605
- Matley's here.
- Yeah.

31:45.837 --> 31:49.375
I would say, based on
our available handwriting evidence...

31:49.574 --> 31:51.952
yes, this is the same person.

31:52.110 --> 31:57.389
This signature on the June 24th document
shows some conspicuous differences.

31:57.783 --> 32:00.889
But it also shows
some inconspicuous...

32:01.086 --> 32:03.464
similarities
to Colonel Killian's handwriting.

32:03.688 --> 32:06.225
Right, and why might
differences like this exist?

32:06.425 --> 32:09.065
The content of the memo
is highly stressful...

32:09.261 --> 32:13.539
Killian telling a higher-up that he
cannot rate Bush during his absence.

32:13.732 --> 32:18.147
This is enough to explain differences
in the pen strokes.

32:21.306 --> 32:23.582
Would you excuse me a moment?

32:26.978 --> 32:29.618
