01:44:47.114 --> 01:44:50.755
He would have to know
or learn all of this...

01:44:50.918 --> 01:44:54.957
in order to fool us
as you assume he did.

01:44:55.122 --> 01:44:56.567
Now...

01:44:57.224 --> 01:44:59.670
do you really think that a man...

01:44:59.827 --> 01:45:02.831
who takes this kind of time
and precision...

01:45:02.997 --> 01:45:06.342
then goes and types these up
on Microsoft Word?

01:45:13.574 --> 01:45:19.149
Our story was about whether Bush
fulfilled his service.

01:45:19.313 --> 01:45:22.260
Nobody wants to talk about that.
They wanna talk about fonts...

01:45:22.416 --> 01:45:24.418
and forgeries
and conspiracy theories.

01:45:24.585 --> 01:45:28.499
Because that's what people do
these days if they don'! Like a story.

01:45:28.656 --> 01:45:30.363
They point and scream.

01:45:30.524 --> 01:45:33.130
They question your politics,
your objectivity. Hell...

01:45:33.294 --> 01:45:34.534
your basic humanity.

01:45:34.762 --> 01:45:38.335
And they hope to God
the truth gets lost in the scrum.

01:45:38.532 --> 01:45:40.273
And when it is finally over...

01:45:40.434 --> 01:45:43.472
and they have kicked
and shouted so loud...

01:45:43.637 --> 01:45:46.982
we can't even remember
what the point was.

01:45:48.209 --> 01:45:50.780
But you didn't prove it.

01:45:52.847 --> 01:45:57.193
You didn't prove Ben Barnes
got the president into the Guard.

01:45:57.484 --> 01:46:00.055
You didn't prove the memos are real.

01:46:00.287 --> 01:46:03.564
The burden of proof is on you.

01:46:03.791 --> 01:46:07.068
By that standard, The <i>Times</i> would
never have run the Pentagon Papers.

01:46:07.228 --> 01:46:09.333
The Post wouldn't have listened
to Deep Throat...

01:46:09.496 --> 01:46:13.706
- Ben Barnes is hardly Deep Throat.
- He's confessed to abusing his power...

01:46:13.868 --> 01:46:16.576
to keep some of the richest,
privileged sons of Texas...

01:46:16.737 --> 01:46:19.047
from getting their asses blown off
in Vietnam.

01:46:19.206 --> 01:46:20.810
Ms. Mapes.

01:46:21.542 --> 01:46:24.079
Don't you think it's possible,
just possible...

01:46:24.812 --> 01:46:26.758
that some of those fine, young...

01:46:26.981 --> 01:46:29.359
privileged men, as you call them...

01:46:29.583 --> 01:46:35.261
got into the National Guard
on their own merit?

01:46:45.332 --> 01:46:48.609
No, sir. No, I do not.

01:47:07.922 --> 01:47:09.458
You had to do it, didn't you?

01:47:10.457 --> 01:47:13.734
In the immortal words of Popeye,
"I am what I am."

01:47:14.595 --> 01:47:17.906
Well. I would have gone with
"To thine own self be true"...

01:47:18.065 --> 01:47:19.942
but Popeye works.

01:47:20.100 --> 01:47:23.309
They'll have their findings in a few weeks.
I'll call you when I hear.

01:47:23.470 --> 01:47:26.747
All right. Thanks.

01:47:29.710 --> 01:47:31.451
Hey, Mary.

01:47:33.047 --> 01:47:34.822
I believe you.

01:47:46.894 --> 01:47:51.104
